        <Classification DateLastEvaluated="2016-03-30">
          <ReviewStatus>criteria provided, single submitter</ReviewStatus>
          <GermlineClassification>Pathogenic</GermlineClassification>
          <Comment>The c.845G&gt;A (p.Cys282Tyr) missense variant is widely recognized as one of the two most common disease-causing variants in the HFE gene. Cys282Tyr homozygotes account for 80-85% of typical patients with Hereditary Hemochromatosis (HH). However, the majority of individuals who are homozygous for this variant do not develop the disease (GeneReviews, Kowdley et al., 2012; Ramrakhiani and Bacon, 1998; and Morrison et al., 2003). In summary, this variant c.845G&gt;A (p.Cys282Tyr) meets our criteria for a Pathogenic classification. We have confirmed this finding in our laboratory using Sanger sequencing.</Comment>
        </Classification>
