          <Comment Type="public">The c.845G&gt;A;p.(Cys282Tyr) missense variant has been observed in affected individual(s) and ClinVar contains an entry for this variant (ClinVar ID: 9; OMIM: 613609.0001; PMID: 20301613; 27659401; 26365338; 19084217; 11040194; 23953397; 26365338) - PS4. Well-established in vitro or in vivo functional studies support a damaging effect on the gene or gene product (PMID: 11040194; 23953397; 9162021; 9356458) - PS3_moderate. The variant is located in a mutational hot spot and/or critical and well-established functional domain (Immunoglobulin C1-set domain) - PM1. The p.(Cys282Tyr) was detected in trans with a pathogenic variant (PMID: 15507752; 17384005; 26244503; 25850353; 25277871; 24401005; 23953397; 32153640; 11478530; 26365338) - PM3_very strong The variant co-segregated with disease in multiple affected family members (PMID: 32153640; 11478530) - PP1. Multiple lines of computational evidence support a deleterious effect on the gene or gene product - PP3. In summary, the currently available evidence indicates that the variant is pathogenic.</Comment>
